value.value: A nitrate exposure (PECO:0007406) involving exposure to limiting amounts or the absence of nitrate (CHEBI:17632).
An inorganic chemical exposure (PECO:0001004) involving the application of a gas or mixture of gases.
A carbon dioxide exposure (PECO:0001020) involving an increased concentration of carbon dioxide (CHEBI:16526).
A stratification exposure (PECO:0001035) involving the absence of, or non-standard exposure to temperature or moisture conditions utilized in the breaking of seed dormancy.
A fungal plant exposure (PECO:0007233) involving the exposure of plant to the pathogen belonging to Glomeromyetes class.
A Glomeromycota exposure (PECO:0001058) involving the exposure of compatible plants to mutualistic arbuscular mycorrhizal fungi.
An inorganic anion exposure (PECO:0001009) involving the application of sodium hydroxide (CHEBI:32145).
An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of polyethylene glycol (CHEBI:46793).
A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) used as a reference  to compare the effects of one or more treatment factors in a study.

definition.value: A control exposure may involve the application of inert factors such as water in an experiment, or no treatment at all.

value.value: An in vitro solid growth medium (PECO:0007262) composed of paper towels.
A chemical fertilizer exposure (PECO:0007086) involving the use of potassium fertilizer as a supplement to study plant responses.
A potassium fertilizer exposure (PECO:0001064) involving the use of potassium chloride fertilizer as a supplement to study plant responses.

definition.value: A pesticide exposure (PECO:0007167) involving the application of a nematicide; a chemical entity or mixture of chemical entities to kill plant-parasitic nematodes.

value.value: A natural fertilizer exposure (PECO:0007087) which is the application of castor meal.

definition.value: Castor meal is a by-product of castor oil production from seeds of the Castor (Ricinus communis) plant and has a high nitrogen content.
A natural fertilizer exposure (PECO:0007087) which is the application of rapeseed meal.
Rapeseed meal is a by-product of rapeseed oil production from seeds of the Rapeseed (Brassica napus L.) plant and has a high protein content.

value.value: A natural fertilizer exposure (PECO:0007087) which is the application of a green manure.

definition.value: Green manure is created by leaving uprooted or sown crop parts to wither on a field so that they serve as a mulch and soil amendment.  The plants used for green manure are often cover crops grown primarily for this purpose.

value.value: A salt exposure (PECO:0007185) which is a treatment with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311) in order to raise the pH of the growing media.
An Ascomycota exposure (PECO:0007107) which is the exposure of a plant the to the pathogen Zymoseptoria tritici.

definition.value: Zymoseptoria tritici (NCBITaxon_1047171) is a causal agent of leaf blotch in wheat.

value.value: A bacterial plant exposure (PECO:0007246) involving exposure of the plant to Rhizobium leguminosarum.

definition.value: Rhizobium leguminosarum is a mutualistic symbiont which has the has the ability to fix free nitrogen from the air.  It is typically applied as a as a seed dressing.

value.value: A plant growth medium exposure (PECO:0007147) involving the growth of plants in an air and/or a mist environment, without the use of soil or an aggregate medium.
A hydroponic plant culture media exposure (PECO:0007067) which is an exposure to Knop's solution during growth.

definition.value: Knop's solution is a nutrient solution used in growth experiments with higher plants and containing definite proportions of calcium nitrate, potassium nitrate, magnesium sulfate, monobasic potassium phosphate, and potassium chloride dissolved in water (https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary).

value.value: The exposure using UV-B light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of 315-280nm.
The exposure using UV-A light either exclusively or as part of a supplemental electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of 380-315nm.
Exposure to the regions with a temperate climate, which are usually characterized by having roughly equally long winters and summers.
A biotic plant exposure (PECO:0007357) involving exposure of a plant to another plant.

definition.value: Suggests the exposure of plant to other plants found in its growth environment. These plants may be growing as a weed or as part of normal farming practices. This treatment is part of an assay of any direct or indirect, harmful or beneficial effect of one plant on another through the production of chemical compounds (allelochemicals) that escape in the environment.  Viridiplantae include all plants from algae through angiosperms.
